Python<pre><code>timed(name: Optional[str] = None, log_output: bool = False, console: Optional[Any] = None, quiet: bool = False, include_args: bool = False, include_result: bool = False, threshold_ms: Optional[float] = None) -&gt; Callable
</code></pre> <p>Decorator to time function execution.</p> <p>Parameters:</p> Name Type Description Default <code>name</code> <code>Optional[str]</code> <p>Custom name for the operation (defaults to function name)</p> <code>None</code> <code>log_output</code> <code>bool</code> <p>If True, log timing to logger</p> <code>False</code> <code>console</code> <code>Optional[Any]</code> <p>Rich console for output (creates one if needed and not quiet)</p> <code>None</code> <code>quiet</code> <code>bool</code> <p>If True, suppress all output</p> <code>False</code> <code>include_args</code> <code>bool</code> <p>If True, include function arguments in output</p> <code>False</code> <code>include_result</code> <code>bool</code> <p>If True, include return value info in output</p> <code>False</code> <code>threshold_ms</code> <code>Optional[float]</code> <p>Only log if duration exceeds this threshold (milliseconds)</p> <code>None</code> <p>Returns:</p> Type Description <code>Callable</code> <p>Decorated function that tracks timing</p> <p>Examples:</p> <p>Basic usage::</p> Text Only<pre><code>@timed()
def process_data(data):
    return transform(data)
</code></pre> <p>With logging::</p> Text Only<pre><code>@timed(log_output=True, threshold_ms=100)
def slow_operation():
    # Only logs if takes &gt; 100ms
    time.sleep(0.2)
</code></pre> <p>With arguments::</p> Text Only<pre><code>@timed(include_args=True, include_result=True)
def api_call(endpoint, method="GET"):
    # Logs: "api_call(endpoint='/users', method='GET') -&gt; 200 (45ms)"
    return response
</code></pre> <p>Class methods::</p> Text Only<pre><code>class Processor:
    @timed(name="Processing")
    def process(self, items):
        return [self.transform(i) for i in items]
</code></pre> Note <p>The timing information is also attached to the function as <code>func._last_timing</code> for programmatic access.</p>
